Here is another way, which you will find in the source code for BeatBox2 on
my website:

http://members.nbci.com/Curt_Esser/

We used the Execute_ command to add our own fonts/ directory like this...

1 Assign a name to the current directory  (Like "Myprog:")
2 Assign FONTS: ADD Myprog:fonts/

Run your program as usual.  Now, Blitz can load you font either from the
normal Fonts: directory, or your program's own fonts/  directory.  This
gives the user the option to copy your font to Fonts: or not, as they
prefer.

DO NOT simply change the FONTS: assign to point to your own fonts/
directory!  This may cause problems with other programs that are running.

To clean up when your program exits, you can use two more Execute_ commands:

1 Assign FONTS: REMOVE Myprog:fonts/
2 Assign Remove Myprog:

Now you can end your program.

