> Yes, that was probably the problem I had.  But, how can you change the path
> inside the .font file?  Is it safe to hack into it with a hex editor?

Yes, it should be. You want to edit the .font file like this:

Offset  Size (bytes)   Description
0       2              ID number, tells you what type of font it is
2       2              Number of fonts in this .font file
4       256            Path/name to font data file (e.g. GoldED/10)
260     2              Font size
262     1              Font style
263     1              Flags
264     Repeats structure starting from the path/name to font data

Just make sure the path is always less than 256 bytes (since you need to 
get a NULL byte in there too). There's a modification to this structure 
where Tags are overlayed at the end of the string (working backwards), so 
if there isn't a NULL at the end, don't go cutting stuff out.

